  "text": "1 It is associated with less risk of recurrence, maintenance of total vaginal length (TVL), pelvic floor repair (PFR) at same setting, avoidance of laparotomy, a shorter hospital stay, decreased blood loss and preservation of coital function. [CITATION_1] Sacrospinous fixation of vault is done regularly at Kathmandu Model Hospital. However, there is lack of published data on this topic from Nepal. We aim to share our early experience of vaginal sacrospinous fixation and its outcome in POP surgery. ",
